</emphasis>
, paratypes: A, male 16 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Mlečnik, Macedonia); B, male 19.5 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Matka, Macedonia); C, female 15.5 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Mlečnik, Macedonia); D, female 18 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Matka, Macedonia); E, male 19.5 mm, phallus with titillator (arrow), dorsal view (Matka, Macedonia). F, 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": HARZ" authorityYear="1969" box="[699,953,1404,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis box="[699,953,1404,1423]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">Troglophilus brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male 15 mm, phallus with titillator (arrow), dorsal view (Olovo, Bosnia).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="6.[144,759,1514,1903]" lastBlockId="6.[806,1422,1514,1903]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">
<emphasis box="[144,251,1514,1535]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">Remarks:</emphasis>
This species was originally described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chopard L" box="[144,327,1544,1566]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" pagination="137 - 139" refId="ref10416" refString="Chopard L. 1934. Diagnoses d'Orthopteres cavernicoles nouveaux. Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France 39: 137 - 139." type="journal article" year="1934">Chopard (1934)</bibRefCitation>
, based on a single female specimen from a cave in the village of Bjeloševina (now in 
<collectingCountry box="[144,285,1606,1627]" name="Serbia" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
). Later on, 
<bibRefCitation author="Chopard L" box="[416,594,1605,1628]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" pagination="509 - 514" refId="ref10439" refString="Chopard L. 1940. Orthopteres cavernicoles recueillis par M. P. Remy en Yougoslavie et en Macedoine. Comparaison entre la distribution des Orthopteres et des Coleopteres cavernicoles d'Europe. VI Congreso Internacional Entomologia, Madrid 6 - 12 Septiembre, 1935: 509 - 514." type="book chapter" year="1940">Chopard (1940)</bibRefCitation>
cited the type series of this species, with the female 
<typeStatus box="[566,663,1636,1658]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" type="adult">two adult</specimenCount>
males and 
<specimenCount box="[334,472,1667,1689]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" type="juvenile">one juvenile</specimenCount>
female. It remains unexplained as to why he did not present the characteristics of the males in his description. As the description is very featureless in most parts and without any illustrations, this led some authors to interpret it differently. Thus, in papers of 
<bibRefCitation author="Karaman Z" box="[462,656,1819,1841]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" pagination="211 - 228" refId="ref10844" refString="Karaman Z. 1958. Spiljski zrikavci Jugoslavije. Godisnji Zbornik Univerziteta Skopje 11: 211 - 228. (In Serbian)." type="journal article" year="1958">Karaman (1958)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Us P" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" pagination="301 - 319" refId="ref11629" refString="Us P. 1970. Prispevek k poznavanju jamskih ortopterov Jugoslavije (Orthoptera - Tettigonoidea). Acta Carsologica SAZU 5: 301 - 319." type="journal article" year="1970">Us (1970)</bibRefCitation>
, some specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kollar" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[451,571,1850,1872]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavicola">
<emphasis box="[451,571,1850,1872]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">T. cavicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were treated as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": HARZ" authorityYear="1969" box="[144,297,1881,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis box="[144,297,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">T. brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The probable reason for this is the specimen of a subadult female of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kollar" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1179,1299,1514,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavicola">
<emphasis box="[1179,1299,1514,1535]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">T. cavicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from locus typicus (collected in the same time as the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": HARZ" authorityYear="1969" box="[888,1042,1575,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis box="[888,1042,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">T. brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and which Z. Karaman received from the National Museum of Natural History in Paris as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": HARZ" authorityYear="1969" box="[838,992,1636,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis box="[838,992,1636,1658]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">T. brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(now in the collection of I. Karaman). It can be justly supposed that this is the same specimen that 
<bibRefCitation author="Chopard L" box="[921,1100,1697,1719]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" pagination="509 - 514" refId="ref10439" refString="Chopard L. 1940. Orthopteres cavernicoles recueillis par M. P. Remy en Yougoslavie et en Macedoine. Comparaison entre la distribution des Orthopteres et des Coleopteres cavernicoles d'Europe. VI Congreso Internacional Entomologia, Madrid 6 - 12 Septiembre, 1935: 509 - 514." type="book chapter" year="1940">Chopard (1940)</bibRefCitation>
cited for the type series. Z. 
<bibRefCitation author="Karaman Z" box="[806,1001,1728,1750]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" pagination="211 - 228" refId="ref10844" refString="Karaman Z. 1958. Spiljski zrikavci Jugoslavije. Godisnji Zbornik Univerziteta Skopje 11: 211 - 228. (In Serbian)." type="journal article" year="1958">Karaman (1958)</bibRefCitation>
treated this specimen as 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": HARZ" authorityYear="1969" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">T. brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as the specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kollar" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[1218,1338,1758,1780]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavicola">
<emphasis box="[1218,1338,1758,1780]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">T. cavicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from a locality in western 
<collectingCountry box="[1021,1097,1789,1811]" name="Serbia" pageId="6" pageNumber="1041">Serbia</collectingCountry>
, where males had somewhat more distinct protrusions of the tenth tergite. Chopard’s undisputed authority should not be ignored in this misunderstanding.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5442333" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5442333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5442333/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" startId="7.[164,243,778,797]" targetBox="[387,1219,196,749]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[164,1442,778,856]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[164,268,778,797]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">Figure 5.</emphasis>
The geographical distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": HARZ" authorityYear="1969" box="[622,876,778,797]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis box="[622,876,778,797]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">Troglophilus brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(circles) and 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1016,1327,778,798]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">
<taxonomicName authority="Karaman &amp; Hammouti &amp; Pavićević &amp; Kiefer &amp; Horvatović &amp; Seitz, 2011" authorityName="Karaman &amp; Hammouti &amp; Pavićević &amp; Kiefer &amp; Horvatović &amp; Seitz" authorityYear="2011" box="[1016,1234,778,798]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zorae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1016,1234,778,798]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">Troglophilus zorae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1240,1327,778,797]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(triangles) (square – literature data). (SLO-Slovenia; CRO-Croatia; BIH-Bosnia and Herzegovina; SRB-Serbia; MNE-Montenegro; BUL-Bulgaria; ALB-Albania; MK-Macedonia; GRE-Greece).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="7.[164,779,932,1903]" lastBlockId="7.[826,1441,932,1107]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">
Unfortunately, we also did not have the opportunity to analyse the type specimen, as it was not found in the museum in Paris (L. Desutter, pers. comm.). The status of this species is additionally complicated by the uncertain location of the type locality. Even in Pljevlja, the closest larger settlement, in northern 
<collectingCountry box="[164,303,1116,1137]" name="Serbia" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
, not many people have heard of a very small and remote village of Bjeloševina. We have been very lucky to find the village and the cave and to collect specimens of two 
<taxonomicName box="[463,699,1208,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[463,606,1208,1229]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">Troglophilus</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
there. One was 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kollar" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[272,392,1238,1260]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavicola">
<emphasis box="[272,392,1238,1260]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. cavicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the other was a species that was well described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Maran J" box="[438,598,1269,1291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" pagination="387 - 393" refId="ref11056" refString="Maran J. 1958. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der geographischen Variabilitat von Troglophilus neglectus Krauss. Orthoptera Raphidophoridae. Acta Entomologica Musei Nationalis Pragae 32: 387 - 393." type="journal article" year="1958">Maran (1958)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maran" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="neglectus" subSpecies="serbicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. neglectus serbicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The similar sympatric appearance of these two, the only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krauss" authorityYear="1879" box="[321,464,1330,1351]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[321,464,1330,1351]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">Troglophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
taxa in the wider region of that part of 
<collectingCountry box="[311,584,1361,1383]" name="Serbia" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">Montenegro and Serbia</collectingCountry>
is common. The dilemma we had was which species of the mentioned two is the synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": HARZ" authorityYear="1969" box="[443,597,1422,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis box="[443,597,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Two points in the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": HARZ" authorityYear="1969" box="[391,545,1452,1474]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis box="[391,545,1452,1474]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
brought us to the conclusion that it is 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maran" authorityYear="1958" box="[404,637,1483,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="neglectus" subSpecies="serbicus">
<emphasis box="[404,637,1483,1505]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. neglectus serbicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The length of the ovipositor in the description completely matches the length of the ovipositor of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maran" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="neglectus" subSpecies="serbicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. neglectus serbicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, whereas it is much longer in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kollar" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[652,772,1575,1596]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavicola">
<emphasis box="[652,772,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. cavicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although this character can vary, we have never found specimens of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kollar" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[397,517,1636,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavicola">
<emphasis box="[397,517,1636,1658]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. cavicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the ovipositor of similar length as in 
<typeStatus box="[456,553,1667,1689]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": HARZ" authorityYear="1969" box="[618,772,1667,1688]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis box="[618,772,1667,1688]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Another detail is the description of the margin of the tenth tergite, which could be treated as the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kollar" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[659,779,1728,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavicola">
<emphasis box="[659,779,1728,1749]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. cavicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
type. However, the observation of truncated apical margin ‘ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">
10 
<superScript attach="left" box="[286,292,1787,1799]" fontSize="5" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">e</superScript>
tergite abdominal un peu tronqué á l’apex, á angles arrondis
</emphasis>
’ (
<bibRefCitation author="Chopard L" box="[387,557,1820,1842]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" pagination="137 - 139" refId="ref10416" refString="Chopard L. 1934. Diagnoses d'Orthopteres cavernicoles nouveaux. Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France 39: 137 - 139." type="journal article" year="1934">Chopard, 1934</bibRefCitation>
) resembles greatly the anatomy of tergites we see in some populations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maran" authorityYear="1958" box="[164,401,1881,1902]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="neglectus" subSpecies="serbicus">
<emphasis box="[164,401,1881,1902]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. neglectus serbicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from western 
<collectingCountry box="[586,660,1881,1903]" name="Serbia" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">Serbia</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[682,766,1881,1903]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="4.[144,223,1236,1255]" captionTargetBox="[409,1159,203,1201]" captionTargetId="figure-247@4.[399,1167,196,1206]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 2. Bayesian inference for the Troglophilus species tree based on the analysis of the 16S sequences. Posterior probability values are shown above the branches when they are&gt; 0.5. Bootstrap values (2000 pseudoreplicates) given by neighbour joining (NJ) and maximum parsimony (MP) are presented below the branches when they are&gt;50% (NJ/MP)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5442327" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5442327/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
). Unfortunately, we have not found females at the type locality. The margin of the tenth tergite in females of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Kollar" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[826,946,993,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cavicola">
<emphasis box="[826,946,993,1015]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. cavicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is always in the form of a shallow concave cavity (
<figureCitation box="[909,1008,1024,1046]" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="15.[164,243,1316,1335]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,196,1286]" captionTargetId="figure-192@15.[323,1283,196,1286]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 12. A–C, Troglophilus cavicola: A, male 18 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Bjeloševina, Montenegro); B, female 18.5 mm, tenth tergite, dorsal view (Bukovik, Macedonia); C, male 18 mm, phallus with titillator (arrow), lateral view (Bjeloševina, Montenegro). D–I ovipositor, lateral view: D, Troglophilus lazaropolensis, female 16.5 mm (Lazaropole, Macedonia); E, Troglophilus cavicola, female 18.5 mm (Bjeloševina, Montenegro); F, Troglophilus zorae sp. nov., paratype female 18 mm (Matka, Macedonia); G, Troglophilus brevicauda, female 15 mm (Olovo, Bosnia); H, Troglophilus ovuliformis, female 19.5 mm (D. Seoca, Montenegro); I, Troglophilus neglectus, female 15 mm (N. Breznica, Macedonia)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5442347" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5442347/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">Fig. 12B</figureCitation>
). This all led us to the conclusion that 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": HARZ" authorityYear="1969" box="[826,980,1055,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevicauda">
<emphasis box="[826,980,1055,1076]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. brevicauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a valid species and that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Maran" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Rhaphidophoridae" genus="Troglophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="neglectus" subSpecies="serbicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1042">T. neglectus serbicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is its junior synonym.
</paragraph>
